{"title": "Souls of Black Folk", "description": "<i>The Souls of Black Folk</i> is a well-known work of African-American literature by activist W.E.B. Du Bois. The book, published in 1903, contains several essays on race, some of which had been previously published in <i>Atlantic Monthly</i> magazine. Du Bois drew from his own experiences to develop this groundbreaking work on being African-American in American society. Outside of its notable place in African-American history, <i>The Souls of Black Folk</i> also holds an important place in social science as one of the first works to deal with sociology. (Summary from Wikipedia)", "duration": 28747, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "1655", "name": "W. E. B. Du Bois"}], "coverArt": "https://www.archive.org/download/LibrivoxCdCoverArt4/Souls_of_Black_Folk_1003.jpg", "copyright_year": "1903", "genres": ["History", "Social Science (Culture & Anthropology)"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "toriasuncle"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "toriasuncle"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Betsie Bush"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "The Forethought & Chapter 1 - Of Our Spiritual Strivings", "readers": [625], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/souls_of_black_folk_librivox/souls_of_black_folk_01_du_bois_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1557}, {"section": 2, "title": "Chapter 2 - Of the Dawn of Freedom, part 1", "readers": [625], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/souls_of_black_folk_librivox/souls_of_black_folk_02-1_du_bois_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1490}, {"section": 3, "title": "Chapter 2 - Of the Dawn of Freedom, part 2", "readers": [625], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/souls_of_black_folk_librivox/souls_of_black_folk_02-2_du_bois_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1400}, {"section": 4, "title": "Chapter 3 - Of Mr. Booker T. Washington and Others", "readers": [625], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/souls_of_black_folk_librivox/souls_of_black_folk_03_du_bois_64kb.mp3", "duratio